<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="470" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d470">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/2337½a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the German Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bernstorff</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 29, 1915</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: The <hi rend="italic">Lusitania</hi> case is causing me anxiety because of the continued
                            suspension of the negotiation. I am loath to make a formal
                            representation to your Government on the subject, as it might cause you
                            embarrassment, but I feel that the time is very near when I will have to
                            do so.</p>
                        <p>I hope, therefore, that you, who appreciate that this state of inaction
                            can not continue much longer, will endeavor to impress your Government
                            with the expediency of reaching a speedy settlement.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>